  "texts": [
    "For instance, Kanjilal et al.",
    "developed an ML model using electronic health records of 10,053 patients with uncomplicated urinary tract infections (UTIs) recorded in Boston from 2007 to 2013, suggesting the most precise antibiotic 51.",
    "Tested retrospectively on 3629 patients with uncomplicated UTI presented to the same hospitals between 2014 and 2016, the algorithm outperformed clinicians, slashing second-line antibiotic usage by 67% 51.",
    "Another example has been demonstrated by Yelin et al.",
    "who developed a ML algorithm able to personalize antibiotic prescriptions based on patient demographics, urine culture history, and drug purchase records 52."
  ],
